Date:7/21/2004 7:15:22 PM
From:Jurgis Bekepuris
Sam,

I did not try to imply that LR or CX has bad or dishonest management. I just
said that these companies have so many partially owned subsidiaries that
understanding the full picture of parent company financials is very difficult
for me. It is compounded by foreign listing, where the results of subsidiaries
are first converted to parent's currency and accounting standards and then has
to be converted again to US currency and accounting standards + adjustments for
ADR ratios, different shares outstanding, etc. As Buffett says, it is outside
my sphere of competence. I bought CX without realizing this, but I would not
buy more of it unless it was vastly vastly undervalued because of this reason.
I am afraid it is the same issue with LR.

Jurgis
